cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about developing a planning mechanism for character-level machine translation using an encoder-decoder architecture with an explicit alignment. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the arXiv sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the model proposed in the paper is end-to-end trainable with fully differentiable operations, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves experiments and analysis of the model's performance, which could place it in the sub-categories of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) and Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV).
